The four colors repeat in a cycle of 4: blue, green, yellow, red, blue, green, yellow, red. This repeating color pattern with period 4 indicates that elements from 4 different groups or threads are interleaved along the M/N dimension. Elements 0 and 4 share the same color (blue), elements 1 and 5 share green, elements 2 and 6 share yellow, elements 3 and 7 share red.

KEY INTERPRETATION:
In K-major interleaved layout, the K dimension is contiguous in memory (stride-1 access along K), while the M/N dimension is the outer dimension. The interleaving (indicated by the repeating color groups) suggests that data belonging to different threads or warps is interleaved every 4 elements along the M/N dimension. This is relevant for warp matrix operations (wmma or mma instructions) where specific data layouts are required for efficient tensor core utilization.


